transcript.text: Welcome to own Print Shop.
In this video, we'll walk you through the powerful new Document Print product type, designed to simplify bulk and multi bit document printing for your customers.
Whether they need to print business reports, training manuals, assignments or internal documents, this new product type offers a streamlined and professional experience.
Let's start by understanding how document print works.
With this setup, customers can directly upload documents in PDFs at the time of placing an order.
Once the file is uploaded, the system automatically reads important details like the total number of pages, helping to instantly calculate pricing based on your configured rules.
This eliminates the need for manual page entry, ensuring greater accuracy and a faster checkout experience.
Customers will also see a real time document preview after upload, allowing them to review their file before proceeding.

They can customize print options such as single sided or double sided printing, black and white or color output, paper types, binding methods, and finishing services, all configured by the admin to match different business needs.
Another exciting feature as the ability to add number and color tabs for better document navigation.
Customers can insert tabs within the document by selecting specific page breaks, choosing a color for the tab, and assigning a number or label to it.
These tabs act as dividers and make printed documents easier to organize and browse, especially for large reports, manuals, or multi section booklets.
This enhances the customer experience by offering greater personalization and professional level finishing options.
Now let's discuss how to set this up from the admin side.
To create a document Print product, go to your Product Management section and select Document Print as the product type.
You'll then configure size settings, upload rules, tab options, and pricing formulas.
Pricing can be flexibly set based on attributes like the number of pages, color references, binding options, and additional finishing like tabs.
Additionally, you can configure Studio events for document print products to deliver a more dynamic and interactive ordering experience.
Studio events let you link specific product options to real time actions within the designer studio.
For example, if a customer selects A portrait orientation, you can bind this choice to a studio event that updates the documents layout and preview accordingly.
Similarly, you can bind other options like size, paper type, or finishing preferences to their respective events, allowing customers to instantly see and adjust their printing selections.

Once your product is published, customers can seamlessly navigate to the Document Print page, upload their file, select printing preferences, add tabs for easier navigation, and place their order, all in just a few intuitive steps.
The Document Print product type helps you expand your service offerings, automate manual processes, and deliver a better, faster, and more customizable experience to your customers.
If you need any assistance setting up Document Print products or configuring Studio events, feel free to reach out to our support team via live chat on onprintshop.com.
Thanks for tuning in.
